cc	-- written, but it needs a lot of work.
  I have a C compiler which generates Vax or 68000 code.
  The Vax code seems to be better than 4.2's C compiler,
  and the compilation time is a little less.  However,
  this compiler is very large.  This is because it was
  originally (and still is also) a Pastel compiler,
  and Pastel (super-hairy extended Pascal)
  is such a complicated lanuage that its
  compiler must be very big.  To compile just C and
  Pascal, a much smaller and simpler compiler would
  suffice, and it would be nice to cut the size down.
  This would mean giving up the ability to compile
  Pastel code.  That is ono great loss, except for one problem:
  most of the compiler is written in Pastel, and we would
  no longer be able to compile it.  So the compiler must
  be rewritten into C, meaning a lot more work.

  A project to write a new portable optimizing compiler
  is now getting started in LA and DC.
